will witness the total solar eclipse of Nov. 3 off the coast of
Brazil, near Rio de Janeiro. Guest scientists aboard ship will lecture
and discuss the eclipse, the constellation known as the Southern Cross
and the so-called Magellanic Clouds. Participants also will see
