<HEADLINE>
 D-Day Celebration at Virginia Beach, Va. 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
No mere day at the beach, that's the D-Day Normandy Commemorative
Celebration Weekend in Virginia Beach, Va., June 3-5.
</P>
<P>
The battle plan for the 50th anniversary weekend includes a Fort
Story commemorative ceremony and re-enactment of the invasion at the
fort's Omaha Beach, June 4; a parade and Stage Door canteen show;
historical displays; and a wreath-laying. The 29th Infantry (Maryland,
Virginia, West Virginia and District of Columbia) was the first unit
to land its troops on Normandy's Omaha Beach. Visitors are advised to
arrive early for the re-enactment. Above events are free. Information:
(800) 822-3224.
