<HEADLINE>
 Harry Houdini's Grave Site Vandalized (New York) 
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Vandals hit Machpelah Cemetery in New York City where
Harry Houdini is buried, knocking over several tombstones and
destroying two carved sandstone benches at the magician's grave site,
officials said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Houdini's tombstone escaped damage but two hand-carved, priceless
stone benches were destroyed, said David Jacobson, who heads the
cemetery, in the borough of Queens. ``They were smashed, they're
irreplacable,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
In the 67 years Houdini has been buried in Machpelah, vandalism has
not been uncommon. Originally the tombstone was topped by a bust of
the magician. But after the theft of the first bust and two
replacements, those responsible for maintenance of the grave site
decided the busts' disappearing act was too costly to go on.
</P>
</TEXT>
