eyes. ``For the last two years, I've been doing another show. I've
been doing Johnny's (Carson's) show. There was something missing from
the show, but I never knew what it was''.
</P>
<P>
In New York, he used a temporary set built in the ``Saturday Night
Live'' studio that packed a smaller audience into a tighter space.
``The audience was half the size, but there was more energy,'' he told
the executives.
