   DDAY-CLINTON -- WASHINGTON -- For President Clinton, the challenge on
the coast of Normandy next month will be a daunting one: to honor one
of history's great military victories as a president who avoided
military service and protested against the United States' last lengthy
war. 1,400 words, by Ann Devroy and John F. Harris (Post) (w). With
DDAY-CLINTON-HONOR, both moved May 20.

