   VINTAGE-POINT -- Choosing the proper wine to go with grilled food.
By Michael Dresser (Sun).

   Home and Gardens:

   HOUSING-ADS -- NARBERTH, Pa. -- Real-estate agents are avoiding terms
in ads such as ``walking distance'' and ``executive living'' for fear
of being charged with housing bias by increasingly vigilant
fair-housing groups and individuals who are filing more and more
discrimination cases over real-estate ads in newspapers. 1,075 words,
by Dale Russakoff (Post) (a). Moved.

   GARDENING -- Cultivating plant buddies that look out for each other.
By Adrienne Cook (Post special). With sidebar GARDENING-TIP (l).
Moved.

   Entertainment and the arts:

   FILM-RAJU -- NEW DELHI, India -- In nothing less than a Cinderella
story, a poor shoeshine boy named Raju was plucked from the slums of
New Delhi to star as a child Buddha in ``Little Buddha,'' the tale of
a Buddhist teacher believed to be reincarnated in three modern-day
children. 1,160 words, by Molly Moore (Post) (e). Moved.

