<TEXT>
<P>
Can't stand the heat? Try the kitchen at the Villa d'Este Hotel on
Lake Como, Italy, for daily cooking demonstrations. Six-day trips
begin Oct. 1, 8 or 15. Each morning, the hotel chef will prepare
lunch; participants can help or just watch. After lunch, guests can
take optional excursions to food markets, vineyards, and cheese- and
salami-making shops. Cost: $1,688 per person, including hotel for six
days, breakfasts and lunches. Not included: round-trip air fare to
Milan and ground transportation. Contact: MSW Columbia Travel, 630
Fifth Ave., Suite 3070, New York 10111; telephone (212) 332-8900.
